---
import { SeasonalChart } from '@/components/charts/SeasonalChart';
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
import { ArrowDown } from 'lucide-react';
---

<!-- Slide 1: Seasonal Intro -->
<section id="seasonal-intro" data-chapter="seasonal-intro" data-nav-label="Chapter 1: Seasons" class="h-screen w-full flex items-center justify-center p-8 snap-start bg-background relative">
    <div class="container max-w-4xl text-center space-y-8">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight lg:text-6xl">Chapter 1: The Rhythm of Seasons</h2>
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            Before we look at the data, ask yourself: <br/>
            <span class="italic text-foreground">Do you feel different in July compared to November?</span>
        </p>
        <p class="text-xl text-muted-foreground max-w-2xl mx-auto">
            We analyzed millions of comments to see if the collective mood of Reddit shifts with the turning of the calendar pages.
        </p>
        <div class="pt-8">
            <a href="#seasonal-chart">
                <Button variant="outline" size="lg" className="gap-2">
                    See the Data <ArrowDown className="h-4 w-4" />
                </Button>
            </a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Slide 2: Seasonal Chart -->
<section id="seasonal-chart" class="h-screen w-full flex flex-col items-center justify-center p-8 snap-start bg-muted/20 relative">
    <div class="container max-w-6xl space-y-8 text-center">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold">Sentiment Over Time</h3>
        <div class="w-full h-[50vh] flex items-center justify-center p-6">
             <SeasonalChart client:visible />
        </div>
         <a href="#seasonal-analysis" class="inline-block pt-4">
            <Button variant="ghost" className="gap-2">
                What does this mean? <ArrowDown className="h-4 w-4" />
            </Button>
        </a>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Slide 3: Seasonal Analysis -->
 <section id="seasonal-analysis" class="h-screen w-full flex items-center justify-center p-8 snap-start bg-background relative">
    <div class="container max-w-4xl space-y-12">
        <div class="space-y-6">
             <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold lg:text-4xl">Summer Highs & Winter Lows</h3>
             <div class="prose dark:prose-invert text-xl max-w-none">
                <p>
                    The data reveals a clear pattern. Sentiment <strong>peaks significantly in June and July</strong>. 
                    This correlates with summer holidays in the Northern Hemisphere, where the majority of Reddit users reside.
                </p>
                <p>
                    In contrast, we see a distinct <strong>dip in November and December</strong>. 
                    Despite the festive season, the "Winter Blues" or Seasonal Affective Disorder (SAD) seems to manifest in digital conversations as well.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex justify-end pt-8">
            <a href="#events-intro">
                <Button size="lg" className="gap-2">
                    Next Chapter: Events <ArrowDown className="h-4 w-4" />
                </Button>
            </a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
